{
  "texts": [
    "Identifying security flaws within the generated code is challenging; developers might not review every piece of code in detail, leading to overlooked errors.",
    "There is also a risk of LLMs being exploited by bad actors who may tamper with the training data or manipulate the prompts used during the query phase [46].",
    "The opaque nature of LLMs adds another layer of complexity to the task of analyzing and debugging automatically generated code.",
    "The intricate algorithms that drive the code generation process are not fully transparent to developers, making it hard for them to grasp how the code comes to exist.",
    "This issue becomes even more pronounced in programming environments where code is continuously edited."
  ]
}